The counterfeit papers were printed with an ordinary color printer.
Of course, the new owners did not receive these for nothing: every migrant who hoped to be able to save the tests paid seven thousand rubles for the document.
That’s more than twice the cost of the official test: it costs migrant workers three thousand rubles.
