Mexicans tend to blame emigrants - they call them hard times in their memory, he says
Navarrete believes Mexican Americans are trapped between two worlds
On a recent trip to Mexico City, I had just crossed the hall and had arrived at the passport check when mischief spread in me.
Signs refer to two waiting strings: one for "Mexicanos" ("Mexicans"), another for "Extranjeros" ("Foreigners").
