This would have done more for the creation of a Palestinian state than for the upcoming application for UN observer status.
Obama must also contribute his part to moving Israel to negotiations.
During his first term of office, he missed the idea of his own peace plan.
Far away in the White House, it seems that he is also distracted by a stake.
But this is a sad, short-sighted perspective.
The United States has a significant interest in a stable Middle East.
And this includes a peace agreement between Israel and the Palestinians.
