As a result, Australia introduces the world’s strictest regulations for tobacco packaging.
The Australian federal government wants to discourage young people from smoking by eliminating the glamorous image of tobacco use.
Studies have shown that people who have not started smoking at 26 years of age are 99% more likely to not start smoking after that.
