"The laws will lead to serious, unintended consequences," says Scott McIntyre of British American Tobacco Australia.
Chinese and Indonesian counterfeiters will offer much larger quantities of these products on Australia’s roads.
Others, on the other hand, say that the laws have boosted their business.
Sandra Ha of Zico Import Pty Ltd, a small family business, notes that the demand for cigarette nets and silicone lids to cover the intolerable packaging has increased enormously since the British American Tobacco Group, Britain's Imperial Tobacco, Philip Morris and Japan have been dealing with two of the tobacco companies.
